claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table displaying percentages of local (pain, firmness/swelling, redness) and systemic (headache, fatigue, muscle pain, joint pain, nausea, shivers/chills, fever) adverse events for two vaccines: Flublok (N=972) and IIV3 (N=967), categorized by any, moderate, and severe events. does not support the claim because the table provides only reactogenicity data and contains no information about production-induced mutations or their effect on vaccine effectiveness. Note: Image is clear but limited to safety/reactogenicity outcomes; no mutation or efficacy details present.
